info.Experiment_date_and_location: Department of Orthopaedics, Karolinska Institute at the Huddinge University Hospital, Sweden.
info.Number_of_markers_per_segment: five on the thigh and six on the shank
info.Marker_location: The five markers on the thigh were placed at 40, and 80% of the distance between greater trochanter and distal end of the lateral femoral condyle. Three of those markers on the thigh were placed along,45, 70, and 95% of the distance between the anterior superior iliac spine and proximal patella. Three markers on the shank were positioned at 20, 60, and 100% of the distance between the proximal end of the lateral tibia1 condyle and lateral malleolus. Other three markers on the shank were attached at 0, 40, and 80% of the distance between the mid-tibia] plateau and the distal end of the tibia
